---
title: CSS Geometric Art
description: An animated solar system built entirely with CSS — orbiting planets, glowing star, no SVG, no JavaScript.
slug: css-art
cssFile: css-art.css
explanation: "Each orbit is an absolutely-centered `<div>` with `border-radius: 50%`. Rotating the orbit div rotates the planet inside it — the planet stays at `top: 50%; left: 0` relative to the orbit, so as the orbit spins, the planet traces a perfect circle. The star's glow uses layered `box-shadow` values. `radial-gradient` on each planet creates a 3D sphere illusion with a single element."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="demo-css-art">
	<div class="solar-system">
		<div class="star-field"></div>
		<div class="star"></div>
		<div class="orbit orbit-1"><div class="planet"></div></div>
		<div class="orbit orbit-2"><div class="planet"></div></div>
		<div class="orbit orbit-3"><div class="planet"></div></div>
		<div class="orbit orbit-4"><div class="planet"></div></div>
	</div>
</div>
{% endblock %}

{% block html_code %}
{%- highlight "html" %}
<div class="solar-system">
  <div class="star"></div>
  <div class="orbit orbit-1">
    <div class="planet"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="orbit orbit-2">
    <div class="planet"></div>
  </div>
</div>
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}

{% block css_code %}
{%- highlight "css" %}
.orbit {
  position: absolute;
  border-radius: 50%;
  top: 50%; left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  animation: orbit-spin linear infinite;
}

.orbit-1 { width: 90px;  height: 90px;  animation-duration: 4s; }
.orbit-2 { width: 156px; height: 156px; animation-duration: 8s; }

.planet {
  position: absolute;
  border-radius: 50%;
  top: 50%; left: 0;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
}

@keyframes orbit-spin {
  to { transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(360deg); }
}
{%- endhighlight %}
{% endblock %}
